Overview
This issue defines the initial database schema for the Vehicle Library, which powers both:

the Reliability Engine

the Listing Analyzer

the Library browsing page

The library will store structured information about vehicle makes, models, and years so the analysis engine can evaluate listings without relying on external lookups every time.

The goal is to design a lightweight, scalable schema optimized for Supabase (Postgres).

Goals
The vehicle library must:

Store vehicle hierarchy (Make → Model → Year)

Track reliability tiers

Store common problems

Store basic vehicle metadata

Support fast lookup by vehicle attributes

Minimize storage requirements

The system should initially focus on popular vehicles, expanding over time.

Core Data Hierarchy
Vehicles follow a hierarchical structure:

Make → Model → Year → Trim (optional)
Example:

Toyota → Camry → 2018 → SE
Toyota → Camry → 2018 → XLE
Trims can be optional in v1 to simplify implementation.

Database Tables
makes
Stores vehicle manufacturers.

Field | Type | Description -- | -- | -- id | uuid | primary key name | text | manufacturer name country | text | country of origin created_at | timestamp | record creation
Example Relationship
makes
  └ models
       └ vehicle_years
            └ common_issues
This structure allows the analysis engine to quickly retrieve:

reliability tier

known issues

expected lifespan

Supabase Table Creation Example
Example SQL:

CREATE TABLE makes (
  id uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  name text NOT NULL,
  country text,
  created_at timestamp DEFAULT now()
);
CREATE TABLE models (
  id uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  make_id uuid REFERENCES makes(id),
  name text NOT NULL,
  category text,
  created_at timestamp DEFAULT now()
);
CREATE TABLE vehicle_years (
  id uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  model_id uuid REFERENCES models(id),
  year integer NOT NULL,
  reliability_tier text,
  average_market_price numeric,
  typical_mileage_lifespan integer,
  created_at timestamp DEFAULT now()
);
Query Example
Example query for retrieving vehicle reliability:

SELECT
m.name AS make,
mo.name AS model,
vy.year,
vy.reliability_tier
FROM vehicle_years vy
JOIN models mo ON vy.model_id = mo.id
JOIN makes m ON mo.make_id = m.id
WHERE m.name = 'Toyota'
AND mo.name = 'Camry'
AND vy.year = 2018;
Storage Strategy
To minimize storage usage:

Store common issues only once per model-year

Avoid storing trims initially

Expand only when needed

Focus on popular vehicles first

The dataset can grow gradually.

Future Schema Extensions
Possible future tables:

trims
vehicle_year → trim
maintenance_costs
Estimated yearly ownership costs.

reliability_scores
Numeric reliability scoring.

market_data
Regional price signals.

Integration With Analysis Engine
The listing analyzer will query the vehicle library to retrieve:

reliability tier

common issues

expected lifespan mileage

typical price signals

This data feeds into the Deal Score Algorithm.

Success Criteria
The schema must:

support fast vehicle lookup

remain easy to expand

minimize database size

integrate cleanly with Supabase

support the reliability scoring system

